With this list you can enter the email addresses of those who are allowed to enter your email address and those who are not.<ol>
<li>When you receive and open a digest message from BYUI_Junkmail_Server@byui.edu listing the quarantined spam you will see four links.<br /><img alt="proofpoint" height="63" src="Images/helpdesk/email/spam/DigestSpam1.jpg" title="DigestSpam" width="467" /></li>
<li>Click on "<strong>Manage Safe/Blocked Senders List</strong>"</li>
<li>You will be directed to the ProofPoint Profile Management. Here you can manage which addresses you want to allow and which ones you want to block.</li>
<li>On the left side of the screen you have your personal setting. The&nbsp;<strong>Safe Senders List</strong>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<strong>Blocked Senders List</strong>.<img alt="proofpoint block safe" height="216" src="Images/helpdesk/email/spam/proofpointlist.jpg" style="color: #000000;" width="209" /></li>
<li>On the top of the page you will see a toolbar. To add new address to the lists just click on&nbsp;<strong>New</strong>.<br /><img height="33" src="Images/helpdesk/email/spam/proofpointtools.jpg" style="color: #000000;" width="503" /></li>
<li>Enter the e-mail address in the text box.<br /><img alt="Proofpoint spam entry" height="61" src="Images/helpdesk/email/spam/enterAddress.jpg" style="color: #000000;" width="381" /></li>
</ol><ol>
